<p>Dear [FIRST_NAME],</p>
<p>This email confirms your appointment for a respiratory test on [APPOINTMENT_DATE] at [APPOINTMENT_TIME] at the Woolcock Clinic.</p>
<p><strong>SMS Confirmation</strong></p>
<p>You will receive a confirmation SMS 72 hours before your appointment. Please reply &lsquo;Yes&rdquo; to confirm your attendance and secure your appointment.</p>
<p><strong>Registration</strong></p>
<p>Please <a href="https://wimr.snapforms.com.au/form/registration?new%20patient=[PATIENT]&amp;adult%20or%20paed=Adult&amp;research%20or%20clinic=Clinic&amp;consult%20or%20sleep=Consult&amp;first%20name=[FIRST_NAME]&amp;last%20name=[LAST_NAME]&amp;dob=[DOB]">click here</a> and complete your registration form before attending for your appointment.</p>
<p><strong>Test Preparation</strong></p>
<p>We advise you withhold from usual respiratory medications before testing. Please read the attached Patient Prep Information sheet carefully for instructions before ceasing medication or altering your routine. If you have any queries please call the clinic on 9114 0000 or consult your physician before stopping medication.</p>
<p><strong>Referral</strong></p>
<p>Please email your referral to <a href="mailto:reception@woolcock.org.au">reception@woolcock.org.au</a> prior to your appointment. Please note that a specialist referral is valid for 3 months and a GP referral is valid for 12 months. Without a valid referral at the time of your consultation/treatment, Medicare will not be able to process your claim.</p>
<p>Approval documentation from your Insurer needs to be provided in the case of a Workers&rsquo; Compensation or Third-Party Claim. If not supplied, payment will need to be made on the day by the patient.</p>
<p><strong>What to bring:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Medicare card/Pensioner card/Concession card/DVA card/Centrelink Health Care card</li>
<li>Test results (for example, blood tests, X-rays, scans)</li>
<li>Medication list</li>
<li>During the COVID pandemic, please ensure that you wear a mask at the clinic. This will help to ensure the safety and wellbeing of yourself and everyone you come in contact with at the clinic.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Screening for COVID 19</strong></p>
<p>Please&nbsp;<strong>do not attend&nbsp;</strong>your appointment if:</p>
<ul>
<li>You have been diagnosed with COVID-19</li>
<li>You have had any of the following&nbsp;<a href="https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/Infectious/covid-19/Pages/frequently-asked-questions.aspx#1-4">symptomsâ€‹</a>&nbsp;in the last 14 days:&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<ul>
<li>fever (37.5&deg; or higher)</li>
<li>cough</li>
<li>sore throat</li>
<li>shortness of breath (difficulty breathing)</li>
<li>runny nose</li>
<li>loss of taste</li>
<li>loss of smell.</li>
</ul>
<li>You have developed any other respiratory symptoms</li>
<li>You have been a contact of someone diagnosed with COVID-19</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>COVID Testing</strong></p>
<p>For the safety of staff and patients, you are required to perform a COVID test before your respiratory test. This can either by a COVID PCR done within 48 hours of the test, or a rapid antigen test performed on site. You can bring your own RAT kit, or purchase one from the Woolcock at the cost of $12.</p>
